[SN]TITLE[SN]
Teenagers knocked down in hit-and-run in Edinburgh

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Two teenagers are in hospital following a hit-and-run in Edinburgh.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The two pedestrians were knocked down in Inchview Terrace in Portobello on Thursday at about 17:40.
A 16-year-old sustained an arm injury, while a 17-year-old suffered an injury to her leg. Both teenagers are being treated at Edinburgh Royal Infirmary.
A Police Scotland spokesman said: "A Volkswagen Golf was involved in a collision with two female pedestrians during the incident."
He added: "The vehicle was recovered a short time later and inquiries are ongoing to trace the driver and any other occupants.
"Anyone with information that can assist officers with their investigation is asked to contact police immediately."
